[2
Source: Russia Today/Agence France Presse 18 Sep 1998
http://www.russiatoday.com/rtoday/news/98091824.html

Tajikistan is facing an epidemic of anthrax, with more than 200 cases
recorded and no means of preventing it, Itar-Tass news agency reported
Friday, quoting health experts. Several regions were reported to be
affected, plus one in neighboring Uzbekistan.
[It's not entirely clear whether these 200 cases were in cattle or
humans - Mod.JW
